<title>UK: Flextech gains on Mirror TV deal talk.</title>
<headline>Flextech gains on Mirror TV deal talk.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in British cable and satellite television company Flextech Plc jumped on Thursday following a report that it was in talks with Mirror Group Plc to form a joint venture for cable TV packages, dealers said.</p>
<p>By 0810 GMT, Flextech shares were up 22-1/2p to 535p in volume of 4193 shares, rebounding from a 29p decline on Wednesday.</p>
<p>A report in the Times newspaper indicated Flextech could join MGN's planned TV production company which would compete with those channels offered by British Sky Broadcasting Group Plc.</p>
<p>BSkyB shares were down 1p at 575p and Mirror Group was also down 1p at 214-1/2.</p>
